l": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bpoldrack/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2021-03-19T14:27:25Z", "updated_at": "2021-07-29T00:07:37Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Problem is: Build a dataset with `add-archive-content` to annex the archive as well as the extracted content using the datalad-archive special remote for extraction.\r\nNow, in a fresh clone that only knows a source for the archive (as opposed to knowing a remote with the extracted content) run a `datalad get .`. This effectively leaves that clone requiring up-to 3 times the space of the content we wanted to get:\r\n- the archive\r\n- the extracted content in `.git/annex/objects`\r\n- an extraction cache in `.git/datalad/tmp`\r\n\r\nI think at least the cache shouldn't be persistent by default. The demand on space seems too surprising for a default. Arguably the same is true for keeping the archive around, when the `get` was called on the extracted content. In any case, the special remote should communicate how to drop the archive and how to use `datalad clean` to remove the cache, if any of those was kept (INFO message to annex).\r\n\r\nStumbled upon this in https://github.com/psychoinformatics-de/datalad-hirni/issues/183\r\n\r\nPing @yarikoptic \r\n\r\nPing @pvavra, so you know where to follow ...\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5519/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5519/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}